item.title: Watch: Woman steals Porsche, runs over owner in Toronto
item.description: A woman reportedly stole a Porsche Cayenne and ran over its owner in Toronto. Video footage shows her expressing interest in buying the car before reversing it into the victim. She fled with an accomplice in a gray Bentley Bentayga. Authorities are seeking public assistance to identify her.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Who was Freddie Owens? South Carolina inmate executed by first lethal injection in 13 years
item.description: Freddie Owens was executed by lethal injection in South Carolina's first execution in 13 years. Sentenced to death for a 1997 murder during a robbery, Owens faced multiple legal challenges up to his final moments. The case brings attention to debates over capital punishment methods and legal processes.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Elon Musk's X names legal representative in Brazil amid ban woes
item.description: Elon Musk's social media platform, X, has named Rachel de Oliveira Conceicao as its legal representative in Brazil to meet Supreme Court requirements. The appointment follows a suspension due to non-compliance with content moderation and local representation laws. The company is now adhering to court-ordered content removal directives.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Who was Ibrahim Aqil? Senior Hezbollah military commander killed in Israeli airstrike
item.description: Ibrahim Aqil, a senior Hezbollah commander and head of the elite Radwan forces, was killed in an Israeli airstrike on Beirut’s southern suburbs. The strike targeted a residential building in the Dahiyeh area, resulting in seven deaths and significant damage to Hezbollah. Aqil was reportedly planning an assault on Israeli territory. Hezbollah has not officially confirmed his death.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Trump shares fake photo of Kamala Harris with Diddy, quickly deletes it
item.description: Donald Trump shared a doctored image of Vice President Kamala Harris with rapper Sean "Diddy" Combs on Truth Social, which he later deleted after backlash. The original photo featured Harris with Montel Williams. This incident highlights ongoing misinformation against Harris, especially amid Combs' legal troubles. Montel Williams criticized the misleading post.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 'Lessons learned...': Secret Service admits 'mission failures' after Trump assassination attempt
item.description: The Secret Service admitted to communication failures and operational lapses during a shooting incident at Donald Trump's rally in Butler, Pennsylvania. Acting director Ronald Rowe Jr stressed the importance of accountability and improving security measures. Disciplinary actions are being considered for involved personnel, with plans to expand the security perimeter to prevent future incidents.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Crumbs the chonky cat gets stuck again, this time trying to escape 'fat camp'
item.description: Kroshik, a chubby Russian cat called 'Crumbs,' made headlines after failing to escape his weight-loss camp. Weighing 17 kg due to an unusual diet, he was rescued from a hospital basement and now stays at Perm's Matroskin Shelter. The shelter aims to bring his weight down to 4.5 kg through diet and exercise.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Election countdown: Early voting begins for the US presidential race
item.description: In-person voting for the presidential election has commenced in Minnesota, South Dakota, and Virginia. This marks the beginning of a crucial six-week period leading up to Election Day. Following a politically turbulent summer, Vice President Kamala Harris is now the Democratic nominee. Enhanced security measures are being implemented nationwide to protect polling sites and workers.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Cat goes missing, travels 800 miles to reunite with owners
item.description: Rayne Beau, a lost cat, managed to travel 800 miles back home after vanishing during a camping trip in Yellowstone National Park. Found exhausted in Roseville, California, he was reunited with his owners through his microchip. This incident emphasizes the vital role of pet microchips in reuniting lost pets with their families.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: $7m bounty on head, slain commander was wanted for 1983 US embassy blast
Trump says Israel will be wiped off the face of Earth if he loses election
item.description: If Kamala Harris wins the election, Israel will face a total annihilation, Trump said. “Rockets will rain down from above until the Iron Dome has been exhausted," Trump said addressing the audience of prominent Jewish Republicans. “I will put it to you very simply and gently: I really haven’t been treated right, but you haven’t been treated right, because you’re putting yourself in great danger," he said.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 'Just hits different': Kamala Harris reacts to Taylor Swift's endorsement
item.description: Vice President Kamala Harris shared her excitement over Taylor Swift's endorsement, praising the singer's courage and cultural influence. Harris also humorously acknowledged their Super Bowl rivalry, with Swift supporting the Kansas City Chiefs and Harris being a San Francisco 49ers fan. The interview was part of a broader effort to engage new audiences.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Olivia Nuzzi's ex-fiance speaks out on journalist's rumored 'affair' with Kennedy Jr
item.description: Olivia Nuzzi's ex-fiance Ryan Lizza has issued a statement after Nuzzi was placed on a leave by New York magazine for her "personal relationship" with Robert F Kennedy Jr. Ryan Lizza who works with the Politico said he would also not do any coverage of Kennedy. "Because of my connection to this story through my ex-fiancee, my editors and I have agreed that I won't be involved in any coverage of Kennedy," the statement read.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Vivek Ramaswamy hints at Ohio governor run at his Springfield town hall
item.description: Vivek Ramaswamy held a town hall in Springfield, Ohio, discussing the migrant crisis and criticizing Biden-Harris administration policies. Around 300 attendees voiced concerns about local resources and safety due to Haitian migrants. Ramaswamy addressed rising racial tensions, attributing them to DEI ideology, and humorously hinted at a potential run for governor of Ohio.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Why Jill Biden joins White House's cabinet meeting, Republicans fume
item.description: ​"We’re grateful that Jill is here today. I heard that clapping — it wasn’t for me — when we came in," Joe Biden said. "And here, across previous administrations, first ladies have attended these meetings and on — for specific reasons. It’s the first time Jill has joined us. And it goes to show how important the issue is, what she’s about to speak to, to both of us."
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Meghan and Harry's California neighbors can't wait for them to move out because...
item.description: Frank McGinity, a Navy vet, said he went to meet the Sussexes to help them settle in when they first came in 2020 but he was rebuffed by their security. "Get off your street. They're not interested," Frank was told by the security at once though Frank was not a trespasser, he wanted to show some local history films to the Sussexes, he said.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: 'I guess I am': Jill Biden says she is 'at peace' after President opted out of election
item.description: First Lady Jill Biden spoke about President Joe Biden's decision to step back from the presidential race, calling it historic and expressing peace with their choice. She emphasized unity and a peaceful transfer of power amid political tensions. Her comments came in light of Donald Trump's ongoing false claims about the 2020 election.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: South Carolina to execute Freddie Owens despite new claims of innocence
item.description: Freddie Eugene Owens faces execution in South Carolina for a 1997 murder despite his co-defendant Steven Golden's recent claim that Owens was not involved. Golden admitted to falsely accusing Owens to avoid his own death sentence. The South Carolina Supreme Court has denied halting the execution despite this new testimony.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Video of Chinese student 'on a hunt for Barron Trump' viral. People call her crazy, delusional
item.description: A Chinese social media influencer has claimed she will be hunting for Barron Trump at New York University's Stern School of Business, where he studies. She described her elaborate plan involving spies and gifts, which has gone viral online. All eyes follow Barron Trump at NYU since he started his class there. The student in the viral video said two bodyguards protect Barron Trump even inside the classroom.
item.dc:creator: TOI World Desk

item.title: Trump ratchets up anti-immigrant rhetoric, says he will go to Springfield
item.description: Springfield, Ohio, famous from The Simpsons, faces tension over a proposed visit by Donald Trump due to his false claims about immigrants. Local Republicans urge him to stay away. Trump continues pushing conspiracy theories on illegal voting ahead of the 2024 elections against Kamala Harris, despite evidence showing non-citizen voting is rare.
item.dc:creator: Chidanand Rajghatta
